From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 5 Mar 2026 01:57:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix diagonal covariance being ~50x slower than full
 covariance
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The diagonal path in compute_vfe_gradients_gpu and its chunked variant
was converting diagonal covariances to full matrices via diag_embed,
then doing full (B,N,N,K,K) transport, torch.linalg.inv, and Cholesky
- completely defeating the purpose of diagonal mode.

Replace with O(K) diagonal formulas:
- Transport: σ_j_t[k] = Σ_l Ω_kl² * σ_j[l] via 3-operand einsum
- KL grad: (μ_i - μ_j_t) / σ_j_t (element-wise, no matrix inverse)
- KL value: diagonal trace/mahal/logdet (no Cholesky)
- Sigma grad: 1/σ_j_t - 1/σ_i (element-wise, no matrix diagonal extraction)

Also fix _compute_kl_matrix_diagonal: eliminate Omega**2 intermediate
tensor and unnecessary .clone() calls on expanded views.

https://claude.ai/code/session_017JmAhA6GzxuEk5QF4Y3cQG
